title: The day has come: CommitStrip finally has its very own online shop!
content:
No strip for today. We're opening the CommitStrip online shop!

It all began in October 2013, when we had this crazy idea: we should publish a book with the blog's best strips. But would coders be interested in such an item? Would the most digital guys in the world buy a book made of actual paper? We weren't so sure to be honest. So what better solution than putting the question out there? We launched the crowdfunding campain, and litterally blitzed through our initial goal in just under two hours. A month later, the funding had risen to nearly €20.000 thanks to you guys! Enough to finance a few projects, like bringing the book to life, manufacturing a few goodies and planning an awesome launch party for the book in Paris!

Now that we've shipped an estimated 1.000 parcels, managed to keep things under control, now that we know everything about postal fees, the time has come to open the CommitStrip Shop. You can call it the CommitShop for short

The primary goal here is to keep the CommitStrip coder spirit alive, while giving you the opportunity to purchase quality items at reasonnable prices. Perfect for your home or office

Of course this will also allow us to inject a bit of money in CommitStrip's development, because we're never out of fresh ideas! Especially for our english readers : we're working on the book in english, and also prepareping posters in english. But you can already order mugs and teeshirsts

Now we're all coders here, so here's the technical stuff: this shop runs on PrestaShop 1.6, with nearly no customization, just a nice choice of settings! And it rocks, to be honest! So there shouldn't be anything bad happening. The skin is even fully responsive! We're the mobile-first kind of guys, you know. Anyway, if you happened to have any suggestions or if you run across any problems, please do leave us a small comment or email at shop@commitstrip.com.

In any case, trust us, we'll do anything we can to make sure you get your orders delivered as quickly as possible!

So what are you waiting for? The CommitShop is waiting!

Go to the CommitShop

title: The applications that completely drain your phone’s battery
content:
It's time we talked about one of the biggest issues of our time, one of the most disastrous curse, I would even go so far as to call it a plague:

THE APPLICATIONS THAT COMPLETELY DRAIN YOUR PHONE'S BATTERY

It's quite a big issue, really.

Obviously, battery life problems are mostly app-related, more than battery related!

37% remaining at noon?

If I catch the app that sucked it all, I'm removing it right away.

That's weird, seems no app is running in the background...

Because yeah, apps are fun. But you have absolutely no idea what they do when you look away.

And trust me, you don't even want to know.

Give it to me, give it to me!

Of course, you can always call a "Battery Saver" app to the rescue...

Listen, I don't know what to do anymore... It's like they are always doing the java dance when I'm not looking!

Don't worry, I know these guys. I've already been downloaded 5 million times, I'm a professional.

But let's face it.

Battery saving apps are a huge sham.

We've seen a few actually making the problem worse!

I mean, it's the pot calling the kettle black, isn't it?

It's not what it looks like... It's just a check...

In any case, installing an app that would run in the background just to check out which apps are running in the background... Something about it smelled fishy.

The truth is, it's really difficult to tell precisely which apps are sucking away your battery life.

So when you just can't taking it anymore, there's only one thing to do.

HARD RESET

Sorry... but it's the only way.

Okay, seems you leave me no choice.

What do you mean...

I'm gonna hard reset and test you one after the other!

Seriously?

Not again!

Hey, mister, you're not the one who has to resync 25 playlists.

Yeah, I'm sick of being a scapegoat here.

There there, hard reset in 3.. 2.. 1..

Wait, you haven't saved yet...

Then patiently, reinstall each app, one by one, and check the battery regularly to detect bad apps...

APP STORE

Well, I don't use a lot of power. And you need me anymore...

Yeah, right. Come in.

TO THE HOME SCREEN

But obviously, nobody does that.

Dammit! 35% at noon! Must be that camera app!

I don't even remember installing this one. I'm getting tired of this.

They really need to show an Energy Performance Index on the store.

title: The problem is not the tool itself
content:
I think we've hit MySQL's limits, it's simply too slow... Let's face it, the amount of data is colossal!

Hmm...

So I was thinking we should switch to NoSQL... I've prepared a 3-month battle plan. Here, look!

Framework refactoring, training workshops, internal tool updates...

Wait a minute, let me just check something...

Just as I thought...

Here you go. It's called an index, and it just made your queries 20 times faster...

Dude, missing indexes? Seriously...

Not sure about your indexes? Take a look at Use the Index Luke!
